thub.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/df668f00e6c08cb63661aacc43d0e83388e2c60d/src/Init/GetElem.lean#L79-L79","name":"«term__[_]_!»","line":79,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Init/GetElem.html#«term__[_]_!»","doc":"The syntax `arr[i]!` gets the `i`'th element of the collection `arr` and\npanics `i` is out of bounds.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/GetElem.html#«term__[_]_!»\"><span class=\"name\">«term__[_]_!»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/df668f00e6c08cb63661aacc43d0e83388e2c60d/src/Init/GetElem.lean#L73-L73","name":"«term__[_]_?»","line":73,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Init/GetElem.html#«term__[_]_?»","doc":"The syntax `arr[i]?` gets the `i`'th element of the collection `arr` or\nreturns `none` if `i` is out of bounds.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/GetElem.html#«term__[_]_?»\"><span class=\"name\">«term__[_]_?»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/df668f00e6c08cb63661aacc43d0e83388e2c60d/src/Init/GetElem.lean#L65-L66","name":"«term__[_]'_»","line":65,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Init/GetElem.html#«term__[_]'_»","doc":"The syntax `arr[i]` gets the `i`'th element of the collection `arr`. If there\nare proof side conditions to the application, they will be automatically\ninferred by the `get_elem_tactic` tactic.\n\nThe actual behavior of this class is type-dependent, but here are some\nimportant implementations:\n* `arr[i] : α` where `arr : Array α` and `i : Nat` or `i : USize`: does array\n  indexing with no bounds check and a proof side goal `i < arr.size`.\n* `l[i] : α` where `l : List α` and `i : Nat`: index into a list, with proof\n  side goal `i < l.length`.\n* `stx[i] : Syntax` where `stx : Syntax` and `i : Nat`: get a syntax argument,\n  no side goal (returns `.missing` out of range)\n\nThere are other variations on this syntax:\n* `arr[i]!` is syntax for `getElem! arr i` which should panic and return\n  `default : α` if the index is not valid.\n* `arr[i]?` is syntax for `getElem?` which should return `none` if the index\n  is not valid.\n* `arr[i]'h` is syntax for `getElem arr i h` with `h` an explicit proof the\n  index is valid.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/GetElem.html#«term__[_]'_»\"><span class=\"name\">«term__[_]'_»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/df668f00e6c08cb63661aacc43d0e83388e2c60d/src/Init/GetElem.lean#L61-L62","name":"«term__[_]»","line":61,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Init/GetElem.html#«term__[_]»","doc":"The syntax `arr[i]` gets the `i`'th element of the collection `arr`. If there\nare proof side conditions to the application, they will be automatically\ninferred by the `get_elem_tactic` tactic.\n\nThe actual behavior of this class is type-dependent, but here are some\nimportant implementations:\n* `arr[i] : α` where `arr : Array α` and `i : Nat` or `i : USize`: does array\n  indexing with no bounds check and a proof side goal `i < arr.size`.\n* `l[i] : α` where `l : List α` and `i : Nat`: index into a list, with proof\n  side goal `i < l.length`.\n* `stx[i] : Syntax` where `stx : Syntax` and `i : Nat`: get a syntax argument,\n  no side goal (returns `.missing` out of range)\n\nThere are other variations on this syntax:\n* `arr[i]!` is syntax for `getElem! arr i` which should panic and return\n  `default : α` if the index is not valid.\n* `arr[i]?` is syntax for `getElem?` which should return `none` if the index\n  is not valid.\n* `arr[i]'h` is syntax for `getElem arr i h` with `h` an explicit proof the\n  index is valid.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/GetElem.html#«term__[_]»\"><span class=\"name\">«term__[_]»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/df668f00e6c08cb63661aacc43d0e83388e2c60d/src/Init/GetElem.lean#L56-L56","name":"GetElem.getElem!","line":56,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Init/GetElem.html#GetElem.getElem!","doc":""},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/GetElem.html#GetElem.getElem!\"><span class=\"name\">GetElem</span>.<span class=\"name\">getElem!</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{coll : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{idx : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> v}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{elem : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#outParam\">outParam</a> <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">(<a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w)</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{valid : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#outParam\">outParam</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">coll</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">idx</span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></span></span>)</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[self : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/GetElem.html#GetElem\">GetElem</a> <span class=\"fn\">coll</span> <span class=\"fn\">idx</span> <span class=\"fn\">elem</span> <span class=\"fn\">valid</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Inhabited\">Inhabited</a> <span class=\"fn\">elem</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(xs : <span class=\"fn\">coll</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(i : <span class=\"fn\">idx</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Decidable\">Decidable</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">valid</span> <span class=\"fn\">xs</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span>)</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">elem</span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/df668f00e6c08cb63661aacc43d0e83388e2c60d/src/Init/GetElem.lean#L53-L53","name":"GetElem.getElem?","line":53,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Init/GetElem.html#GetElem.getElem?","doc":""},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/GetElem.html#GetElem.getElem?\"><span class=\"name\">GetElem</span>.<span class=\"name\">getElem?</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{coll : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{idx : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> v}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{elem : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#outParam\">outParam</a> <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">(<a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w)</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{valid : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#outParam\">outParam</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">coll</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">idx</span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></span></span>)</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[self : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/GetElem.html#GetElem\">GetElem</a> <span class=\"fn\">coll</span> <span class=\"fn\">idx</span> <span class=\"fn\">elem</span> <span class=\"fn\">valid</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(xs : <span class=\"fn\">coll</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(i : <span class=\"fn\">idx</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Decidable\">Decidable</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">valid</span> <span class=\"fn\">xs</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span>)</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <span class=\"fn\">elem</span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/df668f00e6c08cb63661aacc43d0e83388e2c60d/src/Init/GetElem.lean#L51-L51","name":"GetElem.getElem","line":51,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Init/GetElem.html#GetElem.getElem","doc":"The syntax `arr[i]` gets the `i`'th element of the collection `arr`. If there\nare proof side conditions to the application, they will be automatically\ninferred by the `get_elem_tactic` tactic.\n\nThe actual behavior of this class is type-dependent, but here are some\nimportant implementations:\n* `arr[i] : α` where `arr : Array α` and `i : Nat` or `i : USize`: does array\n  indexing with no bounds check and a proof side goal `i < arr.size`.\n* `l[i] : α` where `l : List α` and `i : Nat`: index into a list, with proof\n  side goal `i < l.length`.\n* `stx[i] : Syntax` where `stx : Syntax` and `i : Nat`: get a syntax argument,\n  no side goal (returns `.missing` out of range)\n\nThere are other variations on this syntax:\n* `arr[i]!` is syntax for `getElem! arr i` which should panic and return\n  `default : α` if the index is not valid.\n* `arr[i]?` is syntax for `getElem?` which should return `none` if the index\n  is not valid.\n* `arr[i]'h` is syntax for `getElem arr i h` with `h` an explicit proof the\n  index is valid.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/GetElem.html#GetElem.getElem\"><span class=\"name\">GetElem</span>.<span class=\"name\">getElem</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{coll : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{idx : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> v}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{elem : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#outParam\">outParam</a> <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">(<a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w)</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{valid : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#outParam\">outParam</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">coll</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">idx</span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></span></span>)</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[self : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/GetElem.html#GetElem\">GetElem</a> <span class=\"fn\">coll</span> <span class=\"fn\">idx</span> <span class=\"fn\">elem</span> <span class=\"fn\">valid</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(xs : <span class=\"fn\">coll</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(i : <span class=\"fn\">idx</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(h : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">valid</span> <span class=\"fn\">xs</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">elem</span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/df668f00e6c08cb63661aacc43d0e83388e2c60d/src/Init/GetElem.lean#L27-L27","name":"GetElem.mk","line":27,"kind":"ctor","docLink":"./Init/GetElem.html#GetElem.mk","doc":""},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/GetElem.html#GetElem.mk\"><span class=\"name\">GetElem</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{coll : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{idx : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> v}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{elem : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#outParam\">outParam</a> <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">(<a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w)</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{valid : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#outParam\">outParam</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">coll</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">idx</span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></span></span>)</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(getElem : <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">xs</span> : <span class=\"fn\">coll</span>) → <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">idx</span>) → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">valid</span> <span class=\"fn\">xs</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\">elem</span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(getElem? : <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">xs</span> : <span class=\"fn\">coll</span>) → <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">idx</span>) → <span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">inst</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Decidable\">Decidable</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">valid</span> <span class=\"fn\">xs</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span>)</span></span>] → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <span class=\"fn\">elem</span></span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(getElem! : <span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">inst</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Inhabited\">Inhabited</a> <span class=\"fn\">elem</span></span>] → <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">xs</span> : <span class=\"fn\">coll</span>) → <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">idx</span>) → <span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">inst</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Decidable\">Decidable</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">valid</span> <span class=\"fn\">xs</span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span></span>)</span></span>] → <span class=\"fn\">elem</span></span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/GetElem.html#GetElem\">GetElem</a> <span class=\"fn\">coll</span> <span class=\"fn\">idx</span> <span class=\"fn\">elem</span> <span class=\"fn\">valid</span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/df668f00e6c08cb63661aacc43d0e83388e2c60d/src/Init/GetElem.lean#L27-L57","name":"GetElem","line":27,"kind":"class","docLink":"./Init/GetElem.html#GetElem","doc":"The class `GetElem coll idx elem valid` implements the `xs[i]` notation.\nGiven `xs[i]` with `xs : coll` and `i : idx`, Lean looks for an instance of\n`GetElem coll idx elem valid` and uses this to infer the type of return\nvalue `elem` and side conditions `valid` required to ensure `xs[i]` yields\na valid value of type `elem`.\n\nFor example, the instance for arrays looks like\n`GetElem (Array α) Nat α (fun xs i => i < xs.size)`.\n\nThe proof side-condition `valid xs i` is automatically dispatched by the\n`get_elem_tactic` tactic, which can be extended by adding more clauses to\n`get_elem_tactic_trivial`.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">class</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/GetElem.html#GetElem\"><span class=\"name\">GetElem</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(coll : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(idx : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> v)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(elem : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#outParam\">outParam</a> <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">(<a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w)</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(valid : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#outParam\">outParam</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">coll</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">idx</span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></span></span>)</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> (max (max u v) w)</div></div>"}]}